*   [Agent Operation Authorization](https://datatracker.ietf.org/meeting/125/materials/slides-125-oauth-agent-operation-authorization-02)
*   [OAuth 2.0 Scope Aggregation for Multi-Step AI Agent Workflows](https://datatracker.ietf.org/meeting/125/materials/slides-125-oauth-oauth-20-scope-aggregation-for-multi-step-ai-agent-workflows-00)
*   [OAuth2.0 Extension for Multi-AI Agent Collaboration](https://datatracker.ietf.org/meeting/125/materials/slides-125-oauth-oauth20-extension-for-multi-ai-agent-collaboration-00)

*   **Collaboration:** Multiple presenters (Qing He, Yueni, etc.) discussed extending [draft-ietf-oauth-transaction-tokens](https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/draft-ietf-oauth-transaction-tokens/) and RAR to handle multi-agent collaboration, delegation, and user consent for autonomous agent operations.

## Decisions and Action Items
*   **OAuth 2.1:** General agreement to remove the 'plain' PKCE method.
*   **First-Party Apps:** The working group decided **not** to use/extend PAR for this specification.
*   **First-Party Apps:** The Chairs will prepare for Working Group Last Call (WGLC) once the final PAR-related editorial changes are made.
*   **Hash Algorithms:** The draft will focus on SHA-512 to address immediate regulatory needs (CNSA 2.0) without mandating a complex negotiation framework.

